result.execSummary:
The defendant James A Simcoe was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possesses Illegal Article, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 302.095(2)(b).
  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

[ml] Case called at 2:38PM
Defendant James A Simcoe in court, in custody  with attorney Amber K. Rumpf. ADA Theresa Beck appears for the State of Wisconsin.
This file is scheduled for a Status and Motion hearing, however the Defense files resolution paperwork prior to the case being called.

Maximum penalties are recited; Constitutional rights are reviewed; plea of " GUILTY " entered as to Counts #3 and #5; factual basis stipulated. The Court accepts the plea, finds the Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Counts #1, #2, and #4.

On Counts #3 and #5, the Court withholds sentence and places the Defendant on Probation for 3 years, with conditions:
--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with recommended treatment per Agent
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment, or counseling per Agent
--random drug and/or alcohol screening
--must obtain/maintain employment and/or educational programming
--no possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription
--to take any and all prescription medications only as prescribed by a treating prescriber
--if permitted to travel out of state: no possession or use of marijuana (THC) in states where it is legal.  No legal CBD products or other legal cannabis derivatives without express written permission of the Agent
--payment of all costs, fees, and surcharges (includes drug testing fees in the amount of $75.00; owed jointly and severally with the co-defendants)
--no contact with any known drug offender except for treatment purposes or as deemed appropriate per agent
--no contact with Araceli Granda or Joseph Tadl

The Court orders the Defendant to report to the Jefferson County Probation Department no later than 9:00AM in 06/07/2022.
